cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and machine learning, specifically on improving transfer learning using Convolutional Networks (ConvNets). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of AdaBoost.MH classifier, which falls under the category of machine learning algorithms, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of multiple ConvNet layers and their complementary nature, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on standard datasets, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
